# photo-montage skill — configuration (all optional; copy to your shell env or a
# sourced .env). Nothing is hardcoded; sensible fallbacks apply.

# --- AI backend -------------------------------------------------------------
# Option A: Gemini Developer API key (simplest — Files API for video, TTS, etc.)
# GEMINI_API_KEY=your-key-from-https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
#
# Option B: Vertex AI via gcloud ADC (run `gcloud auth application-default login`).
# Project falls back to GOOGLE_CLOUD_PROJECT, then your ADC default project, so
# this is often unnecessary:
# PHOTO_MONTAGE_VERTEX_PROJECT=my-gcp-project
#
# Gemini 3.x is only served from the "global" endpoint (default). Only change if
# you know a model lives elsewhere:
# VERTEX_MODEL_LOCATION=global
#
# Director/clipper model. Default gemini-3.5-flash; use gemini-3.1-pro-preview
# for large candidate pools (>~60 images):
# PHOTO_MONTAGE_GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-3.5-flash

# --- Photos / output --------------------------------------------------------
# Default album to publish the finished reel into:
# PHOTO_MONTAGE_ALBUM=Montages
#
# Family/shared iCloud album names to also pull candidates from (comma-separated):
# PHOTO_MONTAGE_SHARED_ALBUMS=Family Shared,Trip 2026

# --- Music ------------------------------------------------------------------
# A local or mounted folder of DRM-free tracks (.mp3/.m4a/.flac) the agent picks
# from. E.g. an iTunes/Music folder or a mounted NAS share:
#   PHOTO_MONTAGE_MUSIC_DIR=/Volumes/Media/Music
# If unset, the skill uses Lyria (generated, copyright-clean) or a track you pass
# explicitly to build_reel --music.
